# --- RSVP (production) — Supabase Edge only (no Apps Script URL / webhook in the browser repo) ---
# 1) Create a GCP service account, enable Sheets API, download JSON.
# 2) Share your spreadsheet with the service account email (Editor).
# 3) Supabase Dashboard → Edge Functions → submit-rsvp → Secrets:
#    GOOGLE_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_JSON=<paste full JSON string>
#    RSVP_SPREADSHEET_ID=<from sheet URL>
#    RSVP_SHEET_TAB_NAME=RSVPs   (optional)
# 4) Deploy function: `supabase functions deploy submit-rsvp`
#    (Use supabase/config.toml verify_jwt = false for anonymous guests.)
# 5) Expose anon keys for the frontend (Repository secrets or Actions variables on GitHub):
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://YOUR_PROJECT.supabase.co
VITE_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=eyJ...anon...

# Legacy Google Apps Script + Vite proxy (optional local only — not wired in UI anymore):
# VITE_RSVP_SCRIPT_URL=
# VITE_RSVP_WEBHOOK_SECRET=

# Legacy Supabase project id field (optional if URLs above are set)
VITE_SUPABASE_PROJECT_ID=
